<% include ../partials/header %>
<section>
    <div class="container edit">
        <h3>Hi <%= currentUser.firstName %></h3>
        <p>Here can edit your profile image, and your name (probably useless but I've left it in there). Your image has to be an existing internet link, so I'd recommend that you copy the image from your LinkedIn profile. (Righ click, 'copy image address').</p>
        <form action="/user/<%= currentUser._id %>?_method=PUT" method="POST">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-6">
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label>Image</label>
                        <input class="form-control" type="text" name="user[image]" value="<%= currentUser.image %>" required>
                        <img src="<%= currentUser.image %>" alt="<%= currentUser.firstName %>'s profile image" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label>First Name</label>
                        <input class="form-control" type="text" name="user[firstName]" value="<%= currentUser.firstName %>" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label>Last Name</label>
                        <input class="form-control" type="text" name="user[lastName]" value="<%= currentUser.lastName %>" required>
                    </div>
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <button class="btn btn-lg btn-primary btn-block">Update your profile</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </form>
        <p>What happens next: when you hit 'update' you'll be logged out. You'll have to sign back in again. Then you'll have to update each of your own jobs to see your new image and name represented. Yes it's annoying, but it's the quickest I could sort this out.</p>
    </div>
</section>


